title: Strange Girl Omnibus
description:
'Strange Girl Omnibus'

Image Comics, 2011, 484 pages

Written by Rick Remember

Illustrated by Eric Nguyen, Jerome Opena, Harper Jaten, Nick Stakal, Micah Farritor, Peter Bergting, Andy Kuhn, Brett Blevins

Colored by Joelle Comtois, Tony Avina, Michell Madsen, Russ Lowry

Ten years after the Rapture, a beautiful occultist and her pet demon embark on a road trip to the last open gateway to heaven in hopes of befriending God and escaping hell on earth. A bare-knuckle, action-driven series peppered with social commentary and dark humor, Strange Girl is a story about the bewildering nature of religion, what would happen if the dark future predicted by many came true, and what a good person would endure for not having faith in advance of it.
